      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "#### JEP 525 â€” Structured Concurrency (Sixth Preview)\n\nThis notebook explores the concept of structured concurrency and shows a runnable approximation using standard APIs (CompletableFuture / virtual threads).\nIt also detects whether `java.util.concurrent.StructuredTaskScope` is present (preview) and prints guidance on enabling preview features.\n\nReferences:\n- JEP 525: https://openjdk.org/jeps/525\n- Virtual threads (Loom): https://openjdk.org/jeps/444\n",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "jep525-md-1"
      }
    },
    {
